    SolenoidWithPosition.Position

    A simple sensor that reports the speed.

    A switch is any readable device that has an active state when it is triggered and an inactive state when it isn't.
    TalonSRX
    A motor controlled by a Talon SRX with built-in current sensor, position (angle) sensor, and optional external limit switches wired into the SRX so that it can automatically stop the forward and reverse directions when the limit switches are triggered.
    TalonSRX.Faults
    The set of possible faults that this module can trigger.
    TalonSRX.FeedbackDevice
    The type of feedback sensor used by this Talon controller.
    TalonSRX.StatusFrameRate
    Types of status frame rates.
    TemperatureSensor
    A sensor the reports the temperature.
    ThreeAxisAcceleration
    A set of three immutable acceleration values, one for each axis.
    ThreeAxisAccelerometer
    An accelerometer is a device capable of sensing acceleration.
    TwoAxisAcceleration
    A pair of immutable acceleration values, one for each axis.
    TwoAxisAccelerometer
    An accelerometer is a device capable of sensing acceleration.
    VoltageSensor
    A sensor the reports the voltage.
